### VS Code REST Client Test Examples
### Ensure your application is running at http://localhost:4004

@server = http://localhost:4004
@auth = Authorization: Basic any:any

### 1. Retrieve Current Server Host Configuration
GET {{server}}/odata/v4/datasphere-cli/getHost()
{{auth}}

### 2. Update the Target Datasphere Host
POST {{server}}/odata/v4/datasphere-cli/updateHost
Content-Type: application/json
{{auth}}

{
    "new_host": "https://my-datasphere-tenant.eu10.hcs.cloud.sap"
}

### 3. Retrieve Configured Secrets
GET {{server}}/odata/v4/datasphere-cli/getSecrets()
{{auth}}

### 4. Update the Datasphere Credentials (Secrets)
POST {{server}}/odata/v4/datasphere-cli/updateSecrets
Content-Type: application/json
{{auth}}

{
    "payload": {
        "client_id": "YOUR_CLIENT_ID",
        "client_secret": "YOUR_CLIENT_SECRET",
        "token_url": "YOUR_TOKEN_URL"
    }
}

### 5. Run a Task Chain in a specific space
POST {{server}}/odata/v4/datasphere-cli/runTaskChain
Content-Type: application/json
{{auth}}

{
    "space": "MY_TARGET_SPACE",
    "object": "MY_TASK_CHAIN_NAME"
}

### 6. Get Execution Logs for an object
GET {{server}}/odata/v4/datasphere-cli/getLogs(space='MY_TARGET_SPACE',object='MY_TASK_CHAIN_NAME')
{{auth}}

### 7. Get Details of a specific Log
# Notice the info_level can be 'status', 'all', 'messages' etc.
GET {{server}}/odata/v4/datasphere-cli/getLogDetails(space='MY_TARGET_SPACE',log_id='LOG_ID_FROM_GET_LOGS',info_level='status')
{{auth}}
